title: Teens' Reaction To Social Media Ban, Ultra-Processed Baby Snacks, Rules For E-Bikes | 10 News+
description: To test out what types of content social media platforms are pushing to teenagers, before today’s social media ban kicked in, 10 News+ set up two fake accounts on TikTok - one male, one female, both 14 years old. The fake girl’s account was flooded with make-up tips, dancing videos and instructions on extreme dieting. The fake boy’s account was very different - filled with pranks, sexualised content, and schoolyard brawls.  Network Political Editor Ashleigh Raper sat down with Julie Inman Grant, Australia’s eSafety Commissioner, who opened up about the journey to getting the nationwide under-16s social media ban into effect. Grant admits there will be “teething issues” with the ban’s rollout, and says parents are able to report any incidents of social media platforms not complying with the ban.  10 News+ sat down with teenage girls from St Joseph’s Catholic College on the New South Wales Central Coast who have been saving photos and memories from their favourite apps in preparation for the social media ban for under-16s. Tilly, Coco, Helen and Imogen are aged 14 and 15 years old and label the harmful content spreading online as ‘demoralising’, ‘toxic’, ‘influential’ and ‘unsafe’. They all agree there is a problem, but have differing views on the ban and question if it will work.  Chloe Mowday, an Australian mother of three, has been left in a coma and on life support after travelling overseas for a cosmetic procedure. Mowday went to Vietnam for rhinoplasty, commonly referred to as a ‘nose job’, and some surgery on her eyelids. The day after her procedure, she went downhill and had to be put in an induced coma in hospital, with her organs starting to shut down. title: Queensland Jewellery Store Heist Caught On Camera | 10 News
description: A group of men have smashed their way into a Queensland shopping centre jewellery store overnight and taken off with a stash of jewels.  Four men forced their way into the centre and then the Wallace Bishop storefront before smashing up glass cabinets and fleeing the scene in a vehicle with a large amount of stock.  Police are now urging witnesses or anyone with relevant information, including dashcam or CCTV vision, to come forward as investigations continue. title: Iceland Joins Eurovision 2026 Boycott Over Israel’s Participation Amid Actions In Gaza | 10 News
description: Iceland has withdrawn from the 2026 Eurovision Song Contest after organisers confirmed Israel would be allowed to compete.  Several countries - including Spain, the Netherlands, Ireland and Slovenia - have already pulled out in protest over Israel’s actions in Gaza.  Iceland was among the nations seeking a vote on Israel’s participation, but the EBU declined and introduced new rules limiting government influence.  The country has never won Eurovision but previously placed second in 1999 and 2009.
